<subSubSection id="62B39293C4310CF386FE8145ED8324F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="9EAE188EFE6161ECF93846815D842A8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A352EDF803843AD1DB11B16F4D464B58" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="70D27B55ED17E7A885441B8A60FD0D38" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Parasitic</emphasis>
on living branches of bamboo. 
<emphasis id="3522AC44E3A562DBFA3AC8F94E7A1899" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="D2A3727263BA6F4809C4A22798592D5A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ascostromata</emphasis>
1-6 cm long 
<normalizedToken id="5B68C3559121BBCB2D57A47BF683DF59" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-4 cm wide, solitary, superficial, subglobose, long ellipsoid to irregular, tuberculate, fleshy, white to pinkish, with locules lining the periphery, with dark ostiolate points appearing on surface. 
<emphasis id="B05E20E01470184C01AA675288585EF8" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ascostromatic tissue</emphasis>
thick, pinkish, composed of wide, woven hyphae of textura intricata. 
<emphasis id="88465A72F718B6E7B835C2B1D67DD27D" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Locules</emphasis>
in vertical section 370-700 
<normalizedToken id="74B53BA1A20BF91EACC013699B0C8345" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
high 
<normalizedToken id="B7CF1020CEC1E6BA738AF59F855FC95C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
370-700 
<normalizedToken id="5F8B98E07A0E250397BFB06050A90DC1" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam. (
<emphasis id="2D14C8C78BB9B8C8BD487818746C146B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 541 
<normalizedToken id="94F20A3A7D794BB44D68033E4C37D888" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
513 
<normalizedToken id="E87995306908D92BE950B3B426687CC0" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), globose to subglobose, immersed in the peripheral layer of ascostromata, with 100-200 
<normalizedToken id="A06FE9FFA8A1D06E09B802F054A3E9F3" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide ostioles. 
<emphasis id="F50CFA24FE07AC67E54A8B198B01C4BC" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peridium</emphasis>
20-45 
<normalizedToken id="D0A9A09691E105F3A9DD224A623B3387" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick, composed of several layers of hyaline to light brown, small cells of textura angularis to textura intricata. 
<emphasis id="67DFA6725390583280865D6119AE3DD7" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hamathecium</emphasis>
composed of interthecial, hyaline septate, branched pseudoparaphyses, 1-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="7B41511D3DC79ACFE3CF08C54D1F8B0D" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide. 
<emphasis id="59A82AC8332C8293BCD969B1FF057701" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Asci</emphasis>
200-370 
<normalizedToken id="A99D7D05F5411A8FC0B99C37F1C7CF08" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
20-35 
<normalizedToken id="70D29A57CA3735436007887E9910AE49" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="21CAD86A10BA86B35B235F185E5DB96D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 291.6 
<normalizedToken id="5DF824D965469DE6CC2A33BEC99D6EF1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
26.6 
<normalizedToken id="10F5D0EBC6A4581374C382D2E9668E04" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), 4-6-spored, thick-walled, bitunicate, fissitunicate, cylindrical, short-pedicellate, with an ocular chamber. 
<emphasis id="636AE8B9A3A913E45D7D7CBEB3B1CA19" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ascospores</emphasis>
50-77 
<normalizedToken id="CED728B8B643473BA0900C873D65E793" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15-24 
<normalizedToken id="655EB2CC210B5AB63CF65FF6E536100E" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="F08DCBC521E87217BCBE9F8029B38C41" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 62.3 
<normalizedToken id="05B563A0717927758227647645F545BF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
18.1 
<normalizedToken id="ACD7D224276E2F59579D28F3619ACF7B" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), 1-seriate, overlapped, fusiform, muriform, hyaline, with 7 transverse septa, constricted at the septum, smooth-walled. 
<emphasis id="B37C6CF10752D591CF56ABDE14E3735B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="DB108CF5CFC1D68F8140B01CF37A39AC" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiomata</emphasis>
200-500 
<normalizedToken id="A7B013BABB612FE3A49C03E8C519235E" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
high, 300-400 
<normalizedToken id="326A18EA2729BE7421E74F1DD7237F53" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, loculate, forming within ascostromata, globose to subglobose or irregular. 
<emphasis id="219DD89B2897AA8BDE1F4CB52CBD830E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Wall of locules</emphasis>
20-40 
<normalizedToken id="2400F54E60DB56D654DD2F53CDBDDE82" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick, composed of several layers of hyaline to light brown, small cells of textura intricata. 
<emphasis id="CB407AB12425AF90432BBE7CB5E60448" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiophores</emphasis>
reduced to conidiogenous cells. 
<emphasis id="3CF11B539418315A019AA6E779E0BF77" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
3-6 
<normalizedToken id="96BEFDFD7D6E1ACE438938080C005B59" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 
<normalizedToken id="5E972B335064516B7E95E85CC26E6685" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="3F8A54A36944C9CBB465B89A00B8C64F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 4.7 
<normalizedToken id="4E592F647AB70D5547BD84370D0276EB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.1 
<normalizedToken id="F1E16D598504A266D0F26D9B8E1EF635" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 10), blastic, cylindrical, hyaline, smooth-walled. 
<emphasis id="8A31ADD1DFDD52E240DEC5431CC8ACA9" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conidia</emphasis>
60-80 
<normalizedToken id="4993966FBE3016756A375C6D73B4469E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
19-25 
<normalizedToken id="7DECB8E289BE25AE98AC51A7D33704C5" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="E739F2F52C0E6041E3B21C992D95F363" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">x̄</emphasis>
= 75.4 
<normalizedToken id="D513A8CE74C0A28E1D0C98CF081CCCEF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
23.1 
<normalizedToken id="24951CBF347B5CEE6815ABBE31B1FC88" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 20), fusiform, muriform, hyaline, with irregularly transverse and longitudinal septa, straight to curved, smooth-walled.
</paragraph>
