<bibRefCitation id="0CAAA1371704D3A0D01B6EB68FC0A74C" author="Hennings, P" journalOrPublisher="Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="259 - 280" refId="B16" refString="Hennings, P, 1900. Fungi Japonici. . Botanische Jahrbuecher fuer Systematik, Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie 28: 259 - 280" title="Fungi Japonici." volume="28" year="1900">Hennings (1900)</bibRefCitation>
, based on a collection from Japan. 
<bibRefCitation id="5919651D577E78F8E49AF4AEE78348F7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" author="Liu, YX" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 60" refId="B34" refString="Liu, YX, Hyde, KD, Ariyawansa, HA, Li, WJ, Zhou, DQ, Yang, YL, Chen, YM, Liu, ZY, 2013. Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota). . Phytotaxa 103: 51 - 60" title="Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" volume="103" year="2013">Liu et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
re-examined the holotype with 1-2.5 cm wide ascostromata, which is smaller than the new collections (1-4 cm wide in ascostromata) in China. The holotype has large ascospores compared with the new specimens in this study (75-125 
<normalizedToken id="5AF8E38F4AF6DE7B012FDE5F77C406EF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
23-47 
<normalizedToken id="98C1E4B935EC360EAC7903C16CB10CCD" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
vs. 50-77 
<normalizedToken id="39F476DB9529DD8B0B1EA43BC6D9D599" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
15-24 
<normalizedToken id="1353E16B05210788DEF6D37E2055D325" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
). The epitype designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D88EFEAF2D955D39D2D6E384C7DBC26" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" author="Liu, YX" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 60" refId="B34" refString="Liu, YX, Hyde, KD, Ariyawansa, HA, Li, WJ, Zhou, DQ, Yang, YL, Chen, YM, Liu, ZY, 2013. Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota). . Phytotaxa 103: 51 - 60" title="Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" volume="103" year="2013">Liu et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
